# Computed Field Examples

## Basic Arithmetic Computed Fields
Simple math operations: addition, subtraction, multiplication, division using \`format: computed\`

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "price": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Unit Price ($)"
    },
    "quantity": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Quantity"
    },
    "discount": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Discount ($)"
    },
    "subtotal": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/price * #/properties/quantity"
    },
    "total": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/price * #/properties/quantity - #/properties/discount"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/price"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/quantity"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/discount"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Subtotal (Price × Quantity)",
      "scope": "#/properties/subtotal"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Total (Subtotal − Discount)",
      "scope": "#/properties/total"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- Computed fields use \`"type": "string", "format": "computed"\` in the dataSchema
- The \`description\` field IS the math expression — it references other fields via JSON pointer scopes
- Supported arithmetic operators: \`+\`, \`-\`, \`*\`, \`/\`, \`%\` (modulo), \`^\` (exponent)
- Computed fields are read-only in the UI — users cannot edit them
- Result must be a finite number — NaN or Infinity shows an error

## Conditional Ternary Computed Field
Use the ternary operator (\`? :\`) and \`if()\` function to compute values based on conditions

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "income": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Annual Income ($)"
    },
    "dependents": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Number of Dependents"
    },
    "taxRate": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/income > 50000 ? 25 : 15"
    },
    "taxAmount": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/income > 50000 ? #/properties/income * 0.25 : #/properties/income * 0.15"
    },
    "dependentCredit": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/dependents > 0 ? #/properties/dependents * 500 : 0"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/income"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/dependents"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Tax Rate (%)",
      "scope": "#/properties/taxRate"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Tax Amount ($)",
      "scope": "#/properties/taxAmount"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Dependent Credit ($)",
      "scope": "#/properties/dependentCredit"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- Ternary syntax: \`condition ? trueValue : falseValue\`
- Equivalent function form: \`if(condition, trueValue, falseValue)\`
- Comparison operators: \`>\`, \`<\`, \`>=\`, \`<=\`, \`==\`, \`!=\`
- Logical operators: \`and\`, \`or\`, \`not\` can combine conditions
- Both literal numbers and field references can appear on either side of the ternary

## SUM Array Aggregate
Use \`SUM()\` to total a numeric column across an array of objects (repeating rows)

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "lineItems": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "description": {
            "type": "string",
            "title": "Description"
          },
          "amount": {
            "type": "number",
            "title": "Amount ($)"
          },
          "hours": {
            "type": "number",
            "title": "Hours"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "totalAmount": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "SUM(#/properties/lineItems/amount)"
    },
    "totalHours": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "SUM(#/properties/lineItems/hours)"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/lineItems",
      "label": "Line Items"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Total Amount ($)",
      "scope": "#/properties/totalAmount"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Total Hours",
      "scope": "#/properties/totalHours"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- SUM syntax: \`SUM(#/properties/arrayField/columnName)\`
- SUM iterates all rows in the array and sums the specified column
- Non-numeric values in the column cause a validation error
- SUM must be the ENTIRE expression — cannot combine with arithmetic (e.g., \`SUM(...) * 1.05\` won't work)
- Only \`SUM\` is available as an aggregate — no AVG, COUNT, MIN, MAX aggregates
- The array must contain objects with the referenced property name

## Rounding and Math Functions
Use built-in functions like \`round()\`, \`ceil()\`, \`floor()\`, \`abs()\`, \`roundTo()\` for precise calculations

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "rawAmount": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Raw Amount"
    },
    "taxPercent": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Tax Rate (%)"
    },
    "rounded": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "round(#/properties/rawAmount * #/properties/taxPercent / 100)"
    },
    "roundedTo2": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "roundTo(#/properties/rawAmount * #/properties/taxPercent / 100, 2)"
    },
    "ceiled": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "ceil(#/properties/rawAmount * #/properties/taxPercent / 100)"
    },
    "floored": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "floor(#/properties/rawAmount * #/properties/taxPercent / 100)"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/rawAmount"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/taxPercent"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Tax (rounded to nearest integer)",
      "scope": "#/properties/rounded"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Tax (rounded to 2 decimals)",
      "scope": "#/properties/roundedTo2"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Tax (ceiling — always round up)",
      "scope": "#/properties/ceiled"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Tax (floor — always round down)",
      "scope": "#/properties/floored"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- \`round(x)\` — round to nearest integer
- \`roundTo(x, n)\` — round x to n decimal places (e.g., \`roundTo(x, 2)\` for currency)
- \`ceil(x)\` — smallest integer >= x (always rounds up)
- \`floor(x)\` — largest integer <= x (always rounds down)
- \`abs(x)\` — absolute value
- \`trunc(x)\` — integer part (removes decimals without rounding)
- \`sqrt(x)\` — square root, \`pow(x, y)\` — x to the power of y
- Functions can be nested: \`round(abs(#/properties/a - #/properties/b))\`

## Min/Max Scalar Comparison
Use \`min()\` and \`max()\` functions to compute bounded values, caps, and floors

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "requestedAmount": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Requested Amount ($)"
    },
    "maxAllowance": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Maximum Allowance ($)"
    },
    "approvedAmount": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "min(#/properties/requestedAmount, #/properties/maxAllowance)"
    },
    "bidA": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Bid A ($)"
    },
    "bidB": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Bid B ($)"
    },
    "bidC": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Bid C ($)"
    },
    "lowestBid": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "min(#/properties/bidA, #/properties/bidB, #/properties/bidC)"
    },
    "highestBid": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "max(#/properties/bidA, #/properties/bidB, #/properties/bidC)"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "HelpContent",
      "options": {
        "help": [
          "Reimbursement Calculator"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/requestedAmount"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/maxAllowance"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Approved (lesser of requested vs allowance)",
      "scope": "#/properties/approvedAmount"
    },
    {
      "type": "HelpContent",
      "options": {
        "help": [
          "Bid Comparison"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/bidA"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/bidB"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/bidC"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Lowest Bid",
      "scope": "#/properties/lowestBid"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Highest Bid",
      "scope": "#/properties/highestBid"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- \`min(a, b, ...)\` returns the smallest value among the arguments
- \`max(a, b, ...)\` returns the largest value among the arguments
- Both accept 2 or more arguments — can compare multiple field references or literals
- These are scalar comparisons, NOT array aggregates — each argument is a single value
- Combine with other expressions: \`min(#/properties/x * 2, 1000)\` caps a doubled value at 1000

## Percentage and Ratio Calculations
Compute percentages, ratios, and proportions with proper parenthesized expressions

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "partA": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Category A Amount ($)"
    },
    "partB": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Category B Amount ($)"
    },
    "partC": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Category C Amount ($)"
    },
    "grandTotal": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/partA + #/properties/partB + #/properties/partC"
    },
    "percentA": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "roundTo(#/properties/partA / (#/properties/partA + #/properties/partB + #/properties/partC) * 100, 1)"
    },
    "percentB": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "roundTo(#/properties/partB / (#/properties/partA + #/properties/partB + #/properties/partC) * 100, 1)"
    },
    "percentC": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "roundTo(#/properties/partC / (#/properties/partA + #/properties/partB + #/properties/partC) * 100, 1)"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/partA"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/partB"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/partC"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Grand Total ($)",
      "scope": "#/properties/grandTotal"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Category A (%)",
      "scope": "#/properties/percentA"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Category B (%)",
      "scope": "#/properties/percentB"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Category C (%)",
      "scope": "#/properties/percentC"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- Use parentheses \`()\` to control order of operations — \`a / (b + c)\` divides by the sum
- Without parentheses, \`a / b + c * 100\` follows standard precedence: \`(a/b) + (c*100)\`
- \`roundTo(expr, n)\` rounds the result to n decimal places for clean percentage display
- Division by zero produces Infinity which triggers an error — handle with ternary if needed
- Operator precedence (highest to lowest): \`^\`, \`* / %\`, \`+ -\`, comparisons, \`and\`, \`or\`, \`? :\`

## Nested Ternary and Logical Operators
Chain ternary operators and use \`and\`/\`or\` for multi-condition computed fields

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "score": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Assessment Score (0-100)"
    },
    "yearsExperience": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Years of Experience"
    },
    "grade": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/score >= 90 ? 4 : (#/properties/score >= 80 ? 3 : (#/properties/score >= 70 ? 2 : (#/properties/score >= 60 ? 1 : 0)))"
    },
    "experienceBonus": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/yearsExperience >= 10 ? 20 : (#/properties/yearsExperience >= 5 ? 10 : (#/properties/yearsExperience >= 2 ? 5 : 0))"
    },
    "finalScore": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/score + (#/properties/yearsExperience >= 10 ? 20 : (#/properties/yearsExperience >= 5 ? 10 : (#/properties/yearsExperience >= 2 ? 5 : 0)))"
    },
    "meetsThreshold": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "(#/properties/score >= 70 and #/properties/yearsExperience >= 3) ? 1 : 0"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/score"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/yearsExperience"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Grade (0-4 scale)",
      "scope": "#/properties/grade"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Experience Bonus Points",
      "scope": "#/properties/experienceBonus"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Final Score (with bonus)",
      "scope": "#/properties/finalScore"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Meets Threshold (1=Yes, 0=No)",
      "scope": "#/properties/meetsThreshold"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- Nest ternaries with parentheses: \`a >= 90 ? 4 : (a >= 80 ? 3 : (a >= 70 ? 2 : 0))\`
- Use \`and\` / \`or\` for multi-condition logic: \`(x > 10 and y < 5) ? 1 : 0\`
- Use \`not\` for negation: \`not(x > 10) ? 1 : 0\`
- Results must be numbers — use 1/0 instead of true/false for boolean-like outputs
- Parentheses are critical in nested ternaries to avoid precedence issues
- The \`? :\` operator has the lowest precedence after \`or\`, so \`a > 5 ? b : c\` works without extra parens around the condition

## Grant Eligibility Calculator
Complex real-world example: multi-step grant calculation with tiered rates, caps, and array sums

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "organizationSize": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Number of Employees"
    },
    "annualRevenue": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Annual Revenue ($)"
    },
    "projectCost": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Total Project Cost ($)"
    },
    "expenses": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "category": {
            "type": "string",
            "title": "Expense Category"
          },
          "amount": {
            "type": "number",
            "title": "Amount ($)"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "totalExpenses": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "SUM(#/properties/expenses/amount)"
    },
    "fundingRate": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/organizationSize <= 10 ? 75 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 50 ? 60 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 200 ? 50 : 40))"
    },
    "rawFunding": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/projectCost * (#/properties/organizationSize <= 10 ? 0.75 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 50 ? 0.60 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 200 ? 0.50 : 0.40)))"
    },
    "cappedFunding": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "min(#/properties/projectCost * (#/properties/organizationSize <= 10 ? 0.75 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 50 ? 0.60 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 200 ? 0.50 : 0.40))), 100000)"
    },
    "applicantShare": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/projectCost - min(#/properties/projectCost * (#/properties/organizationSize <= 10 ? 0.75 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 50 ? 0.60 : (#/properties/organizationSize <= 200 ? 0.50 : 0.40))), 100000)"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "HelpContent",
      "options": {
        "markdown": true,
        "help": [
          "## Grant Funding Calculator",
          "Funding rate is based on organization size:",
          "- **1-10 employees**: 75%",
          "- **11-50 employees**: 60%",
          "- **51-200 employees**: 50%",
          "- **200+ employees**: 40%",
          "Maximum grant: **$100,000**"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/organizationSize"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/annualRevenue"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/projectCost"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/expenses",
      "label": "Itemized Expenses"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Total Expenses ($)",
      "scope": "#/properties/totalExpenses"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Funding Rate (%)",
      "scope": "#/properties/fundingRate"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Calculated Funding ($) — before cap",
      "scope": "#/properties/rawFunding"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Approved Funding ($) — capped at $100,000",
      "scope": "#/properties/cappedFunding"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Applicant Share ($)",
      "scope": "#/properties/applicantShare"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- This is a complex real-world pattern combining multiple computed techniques
- Tiered rates use nested ternaries: \`size <= 10 ? 0.75 : (size <= 50 ? 0.60 : ...)\`
- Funding cap uses \`min(calculated, 100000)\` to enforce the maximum
- Applicant share = projectCost - cappedFunding (total minus what the grant covers)
- SUM() is used for the expense array total — but it's standalone (cannot be composed in arithmetic)
- Note: computed fields referencing OTHER computed fields work but depend on React render order
- For critical chaining, repeat the expression inline rather than referencing another computed field

## Exponents, Square Root, and Advanced Math
Use \`^\` exponentiation, \`sqrt()\`, \`pow()\`, \`abs()\`, and constants like \`PI\` for scientific calculations

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "radius": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Radius (m)"
    },
    "circleArea": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "roundTo(PI * #/properties/radius ^ 2, 2)"
    },
    "circumference": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "roundTo(2 * PI * #/properties/radius, 2)"
    },
    "sideA": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Side A (m)"
    },
    "sideB": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Side B (m)"
    },
    "hypotenuse": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "roundTo(sqrt(#/properties/sideA ^ 2 + #/properties/sideB ^ 2), 2)"
    },
    "valueA": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Value A"
    },
    "valueB": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Value B"
    },
    "absoluteDiff": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "abs(#/properties/valueA - #/properties/valueB)"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "HelpContent",
      "options": {
        "help": [
          "Circle Calculations"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/radius"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Area (PI × r²)",
      "scope": "#/properties/circleArea"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Circumference (2 × PI × r)",
      "scope": "#/properties/circumference"
    },
    {
      "type": "HelpContent",
      "options": {
        "help": [
          "Pythagorean Theorem"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/sideA"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/sideB"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Hypotenuse (√(a² + b²))",
      "scope": "#/properties/hypotenuse"
    },
    {
      "type": "HelpContent",
      "options": {
        "help": [
          "Absolute Difference"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/valueA"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/valueB"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Absolute Difference |A - B|",
      "scope": "#/properties/absoluteDiff"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- \`^\` is the exponentiation operator (NOT bitwise XOR like in JavaScript): \`x ^ 2\` = x squared
- \`pow(x, y)\` is equivalent to \`x ^ y\` — use whichever is more readable
- \`sqrt(x)\` — square root; returns NaN for negative numbers (triggers error)
- \`cbrt(x)\` — cube root (available but less common)
- \`abs(x)\` — absolute value, useful for difference calculations
- \`hypot(a, b)\` or \`pyt(a, b)\` — built-in hypotenuse shortcut (equivalent to sqrt(a^2 + b^2))
- Constants: \`PI\` (3.14159...) and \`E\` (2.71828...) are available
- \`exp(x)\` — e^x (Euler's number raised to x)

## Mixed Computed Fields Overview
Comprehensive example combining arithmetic, ternary conditions, and SUM aggregation in one form

### Data schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "x": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "X"
    },
    "y": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Y"
    },
    "z": {
      "type": "number",
      "title": "Z"
    },
    "arr": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "c3": {
            "type": "number",
            "title": "C3"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "total": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/x * #/properties/y + #/properties/z"
    },
    "condition": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "#/properties/x > 10 ? #/properties/y : #/properties/z"
    },
    "sumC3": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "computed",
      "description": "SUM(#/properties/arr/c3)"
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`

### UI schema
\`\`\`json
{
  "type": "VerticalLayout",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/x"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/y"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/z"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "scope": "#/properties/arr",
      "label": "Array of objects"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Total (x × y + z)",
      "scope": "#/properties/total"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Condition (if x > 10 then y else z)",
      "scope": "#/properties/condition"
    },
    {
      "type": "Control",
      "label": "Sum of C3",
      "scope": "#/properties/sumC3"
    }
  ]
}
\`\`\`

### Notes
- Demonstrates three computed patterns in one form: arithmetic, ternary condition, and SUM aggregate
- Arithmetic: \`#/properties/x * #/properties/y + #/properties/z\` — standard operator precedence (* before +)
- Ternary: \`#/properties/x > 10 ? #/properties/y : #/properties/z\` — returns y if x>10, else z
- SUM: \`SUM(#/properties/arr/c3)\` — sums the c3 column across all array rows
- Computed fields render as read-only inputs that update automatically as users enter data
- The \`description\` field holds the expression — it doubles as tooltip text in some renderers

# Anti-Patterns — What NOT To Do
Common mistakes and pitfalls to avoid when generating JSON Forms configuration

## Schema Anti-Patterns
### ❌ UI Schema Scope Mismatch (critical)
UI schema Control references a property that doesn't exist in the data schema

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "firstName": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "#/properties/first_name"
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "firstName": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "#/properties/firstName"
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** The scope \`#/properties/first_name\` uses snake_case but the data schema property is \`firstName\` (camelCase). Scopes must exactly match property names.

### ❌ Missing Scope Prefix (critical)
Control scope doesn't start with \`#/properties/\`

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "firstName"
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "#/properties/firstName"
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** Every Control scope must be a JSON pointer starting with \`#/properties/\`. Omitting the prefix causes the control to not render.

### ❌ Non-camelCase Property Names (high)
Using snake_case, PascalCase, or spaces in data schema property names

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "first_name": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "LastName": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "phone number": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "firstName": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "lastName": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "phoneNumber": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** Always use camelCase for property names. This is the convention for JSON Forms and ensures consistency in scope references.

### ❌ Missing Pages Variant on Categorization (medium)
Using Categorization without specifying the pages variant

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Categorization",
    "elements": [
      {
        "type": "Category",
        "label": "Step 1",
        "elements": []
      }
    ]
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Categorization",
    "options": {
      "variant": "pages"
    },
    "elements": [
      {
        "type": "Category",
        "label": "Step 1",
        "elements": []
      }
    ]
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** For multi-page forms, always set \`options.variant\` to \`"pages"\` on the Categorization element. Without it, pages won't render as steps.

### ❌ Required Field Not in Properties (high)
Listing a field in \`required\` that doesn't exist as a property

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "email": {
        "type": "string",
        "format": "email"
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "email",
      "name"
    ]
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "email": {
        "type": "string",
        "format": "email"
      },
      "name": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "email",
      "name"
    ]
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** Every field listed in \`required\` must also exist in \`properties\`. An orphaned required field causes validation errors.

### ❌ Including formDefinitionId in Tool Input (critical)
Passing formDefinitionId as input to formConfigurationUpdateTool

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "toolInput": {
    "formDefinitionId": "my-form-id",
    "name": "My Form",
    "dataSchema": {}
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "toolInput": {
    "name": "My Form",
    "dataSchema": {}
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** formDefinitionId comes from request context automatically. Including it in tool input causes an error. Only pass name, dataSchema, uiSchema, anonymousApply, applicantRoles, and assessorRoles.

## Design Anti-Patterns
### ❌ Too Many Fields on a Single Page (medium)
Putting 6+ fields in a VerticalLayout without pagination
**Fix:** Use Categorization with \`variant: "pages"\` when you have 6 or more fields. Group related fields into separate Category pages.

### ❌ No Help Text on Complex Fields (medium)
Omitting contextual help for fields that need explanation
**Fix:** Add \`options.help\` to Controls for fields where users might be uncertain what to enter. Use HelpContent elements for section-level guidance.

### ❌ Including Full JSON in Chat Response (low)
Showing the entire data/UI schema JSON to the user instead of applying it
**Fix:** Apply changes using formConfigurationUpdateTool and describe what changed in plain language. Only show JSON if the user explicitly asks for it.

### ❌ Missing FOIP Notice on Government Forms (high)
Government forms that collect personal information without a privacy/FOIP collection notice
**Fix:** Add a HelpContent with markdown containing the Notice of Collection under FOIP Act Section 33(c). Place it on the final page before the declaration checkbox.

### ❌ Using Default Checkbox for Yes/No Questions (low)
Rendering a yes/no question as a plain checkbox instead of Yes/No radio buttons
**Fix:** Use \`options.format: "radio"\` with \`textForTrue: "Yes"\` and \`textForFalse: "No"\` for clear binary questions. Plain checkboxes are ambiguous — unchecked could mean 'no' or 'not yet answered'.

### ❌ Using Dropdown for 2-3 Options (low)
Using a dropdown menu when there are only 2-3 options — radio buttons are clearer
**Fix:** Use \`options.format: "radio"\` for 2-3 options so all choices are visible without clicking. Reserve dropdowns for 4+ options.

### ❌ Using Deprecated HelpContent Variants (hyperlink/img) (high)
Using \`variant: hyperlink\` or \`variant: img\` on HelpContent — these are deprecated
**Fix:** Use markdown HelpContent instead. For links: \`{ "markdown": true, "help": ["[Link text](url)"] }\`. For images: \`{ "markdown": true, "help": ["![Alt text](image-url)"] }\`.

## Additional Schema Anti-Patterns
### ❌ Required String Without minLength Workaround (critical)
Marking a string field as required but not adding \`minLength: 1\` — empty strings pass validation

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "firstName": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "firstName"
    ]
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "firstName": {
        "type": "string",
        "minLength": 1
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "firstName"
    ]
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** JSON Forms has a known bug where an empty string satisfies the \`required\` rule. Always add \`minLength: 1\` to required string fields as a workaround.

### ❌ SHOW/HIDE Rule Without Conditional Validation (critical)
Using a SHOW/HIDE rule on a required field without adding if/then conditional validation in the data schema

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "hasChildren": {
        "type": "boolean"
      },
      "childsName": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "hasChildren",
      "childsName"
    ]
  },
  "uiSchema_note": "childsName has SHOW rule based on hasChildren, but childsName is always required in data schema"
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "dataSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "hasChildren": {
        "type": "boolean"
      },
      "childsName": {
        "type": "string",
        "minLength": 1
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "hasChildren"
    ],
    "if": {
      "properties": {
        "hasChildren": {
          "const": true
        }
      }
    },
    "then": {
      "required": [
        "childsName"
      ]
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** Hidden required fields cause form validation to fail silently because the user cannot fill them in. Always pair SHOW/HIDE rules with if/then conditional required in the data schema.

### ❌ Nested Object Scope Missing Full Path (critical)
Using a flat scope for a nested object property instead of the full JSON pointer path

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "#/properties/firstName"
  },
  "note": "When firstName is nested under a 'name' object"
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "#/properties/name/properties/firstName"
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** When data schema uses nested objects (e.g., \`name.firstName\`), UI schema scopes must include the full path. Using \`#/properties/firstName\` when the property is at \`properties.name.properties.firstName\` will not render.

### ❌ Rule Condition Scope Points to Wrong Field (high)
The rule's condition scope references a non-existent or wrong property

**Bad:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "#/properties/childsName",
    "rule": {
      "effect": "SHOW",
      "condition": {
        "scope": "#/properties/children",
        "schema": {
          "const": true
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Good:**
\`\`\`json
{
  "uiSchema": {
    "type": "Control",
    "scope": "#/properties/childsName",
    "rule": {
      "effect": "SHOW",
      "condition": {
        "scope": "#/properties/hasChildren",
        "schema": {
          "const": true
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
\`\`\`
**Why:** If the condition scope resolves to undefined, JSON Schema validation succeeds and the condition evaluates to true — the rule always fires. Make sure the condition scope matches an actual property name in the data schema.
"
`;
